        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Why?\r\n\r\nHere are some concrete examples of where I would've like to have this for performance:\r\n+ In [ultimate-autopair.nvim](https://github.com/altermo/ultimate-autopair.nvim): there's a system for ignoring pairs outside of current lang, as in ignoring regions where child-langs are; and this doesn't require parsing the child-langs.\r\n+ In incremental selection neovim feature: currently the whole visual region is parsed, even when not needed. Example: if the whole buffer is selected and a `select_child()` runs, then everything gets parsed (can be a problem in code with lot of comments...), even though only 0 or 1 (in most cases) of the child-langs needs to be parsed.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-12T20:12:18Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38941#issuecomment-4232656668",
            "id": 4232656668,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38941",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM78STcc",
            "performed_via_github_app": null,
