        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> there's a system for ignoring pairs outside of current lang, as in ignoring regions where child-langs are; and this doesn't require parsing the child-langs.\n\nI'm struggling to understand why you need to know the injected regions for this. The pairs should be detected with query files on the parse tree, so I don't know when you would need to know the injection region. Do you have a more useful example to demonstrate this?",
